CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper December 28, 1946, pg. 3, reads: "Hear Complaints - Carl Beck, 6673 Northumberland Street, Dee Douglass, 214 North Bellefield Street, and Neal Bassett, 700 Hastings Street, hear the views of one of the occupants of 2262 Humber Way regarding housing conditions in the area. Bassett is secretary-treasurer of the group which toured the Hill Monday on behalf of the Hill District People's Forum. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Carl Beck, Dee Douglass, and Neal Bassett standing in front of woman standing in doorway of home with "2247" written on side, 2262 Humber Way, Hill District
